				\begin{document}$${\mathrm{PbBr}}_{\mathrm{2}} + {\mathrm{CsBr}} \to {\mathrm{CsPbBr}}_{\mathrm{3}}$$\end{document}The melting point of CsPbBr3 is about 567 oC, and its sublimation starts when it is melted30,31. Therefore, when the temperature was heated up to 600 oC, the large CsPbBr3 crystals started melting and sublimating, which filled into the pores of MS and formed CsPbBr3 NCs when the temperature was cooling down. Simultaneously, the pores of MS started to collapse and finally fused into a dense SiO2 solid at high temperatures. The sealed SiO2 nanopore not only confined the growth of CsPbBr3 NCs, but also protected the formed CsPbBr3 NCs from oxidation and inter-particles fusion at high temperature.
